               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18461026-name-663" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18461026-name-663" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18461026-name-663" type="surname" value="BRADSHAW"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18461026-name-663" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS BRADSHAW</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable T</hi> 130.) On the 12th of Oct, a little after eleven o'clock in the morning, I was in Vauxhall-bridge-road, and saw the prisoner pass Mr. Cook's shop once or twice—he then turned back, went in at the door, and reached a pair of boots out of the window, put them under his jacket, and came out—he was going towards Vauxhall-bridge—he looked</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184610260084"></xptr>
               <p>over the road and saw me—he turned back and threw the boots into the shop and ran away—I followed about 400 yards, and took him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18461026-name-664" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18461026-name-664" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18461026-name-664" type="surname" value="COOK"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18461026-name-664" type="given" value="GEORGE JOHN"></interp>GEORGE JOHN COOK</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Vauxhall-bridge-road. At a little after eleven o'clock, on the morning of the 12th of Oct., I saw some one come into the shop—I did not see what he did, but I saw him go out—I went into the shop, and the boots were gone—I went to the door, the prisoner came back to the door, and threw the boots in—they are mine—I saw him pursued by the policeman.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I was walking two or three streets from the shop; the officer run round the corner and took me.</p>
